Elliott-R-B.  Eyre-J.  Robinson-P-G.

Salivary amylase in the parents of children with cystic fibrosis.

AMYLASES: an.  CYSTIC-FIBROSIS: fg.  PARENTS.  SALIVA: en.

FEMALE.  HETEROZYGOTE.  HUMAN.  MALE.  SALIVATION.

Mixed submaxillary/sublingual saliva from obligate heterozygotes for
cystic fibrosis shows significantly elevated concentration of
amylase at high or low salivation rates compared with normals.
Sixty per cent of known carriers had values outside the range of
apparently normal controls.

